    "comment": "Rationale: Fig. 1. NPY inhibits 4AP- and KCl-evoked glutamate release from rat cerebrocortical synaptosomes\nFig. 2. NPY-mediated inhibition of 4AP-evoked glutamate release is mimicked by the selective NPY Y1 receptor agonist and is blocked by the selective NPY Y1 receptor antagonist.\nFig. 4. Release inhibition by NPY is due to a reduction in the depolarization-evoked rise in [Ca2+]C.\nFig. 5. NPY does not alter the synaptosomal membrane potential.. Experimental description: - \"Synaptosomes were purified as described previously (Sihra, 1997). Briefly, the cerebral cortex from 2-month-old male Sprague-Dawley rats\"",
